&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be a key member of our team in Zambia, responsible for leading project planning efforts across the organization. You will work closely with business and technical teams to develop, maintain, and optimize project schedules, ensuring alignment with overall strategic goals. Additionally, you will provide analytical insights and planning tools to monitor project performance and support data-driven decision-making. Since KoBold is a startup company operating globally, your role will be dynamic and your role and responsibilities will grow as the company grows.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Project Planner will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead development of integrated, resource-loaded master schedules (Primavera P6) from concept through commissioning and close out, aligned to WBS/CBS standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish the schedule governance model (coding structures, calendars, fragnets, interfaces, and data quality checks) for all workstreams and contractors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive baseline development (scope freeze assumptions, logic, critical/near‑critical path, milestones) and obtain formal approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain robust WBS/OBS/RBS structures and activity coding to enable multi-level reporting (program; project; area; system; subsystem).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform logic integrity audits (lags, open ends, constraints, out‑of‑sequence work) and enforce schedule hygiene standards (DCMA 14‑point compliance).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement resource and crew planning, leveling/stacking rules, and labor/equipment calendars consistent with field realities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct critical path and driving-path analysis, total/ free float consumption tracking, and pathway-of-risk reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run trend analysis (SPI(t), schedule variance, progress curves, productivity indices) and produce leading indicators and early‑warning signals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build what‑if simulations and scenario models (alternate execution sequences, resequencing for access/permits, weather or logistics constraints).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform probabilistic schedule risk analysis (e.g., Monte Carlo) to quantify P‑dates, confidence levels, and criticality/sensitivity indices; propose mitigation and contingency plans.&lt;/li&gt;
